    "pre_narrative": "### **MISSION BRIEFING: THE STANDOFF**\n\n**DATE:** December 29, 2025\n**LOCATION:** Supreme Court of Nova Scotia\n**CASE:** *R. v. Francis*\n\nThe province is in crisis. On December 4, the Justice Minister ordered a massive crackdown on 'unauthorized' cannabis dispensaries. The RCMP raided **Leo’s Trading Post**, a popular shop located on the Millbrook First Nation.\n\nThe raid did not go as planned. \n\nThe community responded instantly. They blocked the road with pickup trucks and red dresses. They lit a **Sacred Fire** in the doorway of the shop, declaring the police were trespassing on unceded territory. The Chief passed a Band Council Resolution (BCR) banning provincial enforcement on the land. \n\n**YOUR JOB:**\nYou are a clerk for the Chief Justice. You must navigate a complex web of 18th-century promises and 21st-century realities. \n\n**Does the Treaty of 1752 give Leo the right to sell cannabis without a provincial license?**\n\n* **The Province says:** \"No. Public safety requires strict regulation. The Treaty doesn't cover drugs.\"\n* **Leo says:** \"Yes. My ancestors signed a treaty that allows me to trade freely to earn a livelihood.\"\n\nReview the evidence. Apply the tests. Decide the law.",
